<br>
Also, just because I have red hair doesnt mean im Irish!  Im Italian damn it, hehe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=feedsravens>Feeds Ravens</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/03 9:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=235.topic&index=62>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/users/k/e/kel142/images/ezboardraven.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: racism</span><hr size=1> Coppertop -<br>
<br>
It can be rough dealing with racist family members - my family isn't overtly racist, but there's a lot of derrogatory comments made in &quot;private&quot; and a general disdain for people these family members consider &quot;stereotypical&quot; minorities.  *sigh*  It could be worse, it could be better, I guess.  Heh.  My family's Italian too.  (And believe me, I know some naturally red-headed Italians.  *Grins*)<br>
<br>
The thing to do is honestly not to fight them if yer gonna get thrown out of the house.  It won't be long probably before you're on your own after school, or at least able to if the need arose.  Then you have the footing to be openly true to your friends and let the cards fall where they may when it comes to your family.<br>
